# Finance Dashboard Backend API Documentation

## Base URL

Local Development

```
http://localhost:5000/api
```

Production (if deployed)

```
https://finance-data-processing-pnk3.onrender.com/api
```

---

# Authentication

Most endpoints require authentication using JSON Web Tokens (JWT).

After logging in, include the token in the request headers.

Header format:

```
Authorization: Bearer <your_token>
```

Example:

```
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9
```

---

# User Roles

The system supports role-based access control.

| Role    | Description                                                       |
| ------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Viewer  | Can access dashboard summaries only                               |
| Analyst | Can view financial records and dashboard data                     |
| Admin   | Can manage users and perform full CRUD operations on transactions |

---

# Authentication APIs

## Register User

Create a new user account.

Endpoint

```
POST /api/auth/register
```

Request Body

```
{
  "name": "Aman",
  "email": "aman@example.com",
  "password": "123456"
}
```

Response

```
{
  "message": "User registered successfully"
}
```

---

## Login User

Authenticate a user and return a JWT token.

Endpoint

```
POST /api/auth/login
```

Request Body

```
{
  "email": "aman@example.com",
  "password": "123456"
}
```

Response

```
{
  "token": "jwt_token_here"
}
```

---

# Transaction APIs

These endpoints manage financial records.

---

## Create Transaction

Creates a new financial record.

Endpoint

```
POST /api/transactions
```

Access Level

Admin only

Headers

```
Authorization: Bearer token
```

Request Body

```
{
  "amount": 5000,
  "type": "income",
  "category": "salary",
  "date": "2026-04-01",
  "notes": "Monthly salary"
}
```

Response

```
{
  "_id": "transaction_id",
  "amount": 5000,
  "type": "income",
  "category": "salary",
  "date": "2026-04-01",
  "notes": "Monthly salary"
}
```

---

## Get Transactions

Returns a list of financial transactions.

Endpoint

```
GET /api/transactions
```

Access Level

Analyst, Admin

Query Parameters

| Parameter | Description        |
| --------- | ------------------ |
| type      | income or expense  |
| category  | filter by category |
| startDate | filter from date   |
| endDate   | filter until date  |

Example

```
GET /api/transactions?type=expense
```

Response

```
[
  {
    "_id": "transaction_id",
    "amount": 500,
    "type": "expense",
    "category": "food",
    "date": "2026-04-01"
  }
]
```

---

## Update Transaction

Updates an existing financial record.

Endpoint

```
PUT /api/transactions/:id
```

Access Level

Admin only

Request Body

```
{
  "amount": 600
}
```

Response

```
{
  "message": "Transaction updated successfully"
}
```

---

## Delete Transaction

Deletes a financial record.

Endpoint

```
DELETE /api/transactions/:id
```

Access Level

Admin only

Response

```
{
  "message": "Transaction deleted successfully"
}
```

